{
  "texts": [
    "A similar first-order character is also visible at the Z + q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM ↔ Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM transition for small J 2 /J 1 > 0.5 (panels (b),(c)), as well as at the low-T transitions at J 2 /J 1 = 0.5 (panels (c),(f)).On the other hand, the Z + q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM ↔ Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM transition at larger J 2 /J 1 requires a more careful analysis.",
    "Using a grid spacing of 10 -6, we find that the transition for J 2 /J 1 ≳ 0.51 is continuous, as evidenced both by the free energy (not shown) and by the behavior of the average effective spin angle Θ:= arg ⟨e iθ ⟩, where ⟨e iθ ⟩ is computed at a representative CTMRG site.",
    "In Fig. 9(g), we plot cos(qΘ) across the transition for three representative values of J 2 /J 1: 0.51, 0.52, and 0.525.",
    "Within the Z ± q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phases, cos(qΘ) takes values ±1, respectively.",
    "While cos(qΘ) remains smooth across the transition for J 2 /J 1 = 0.52 and 0.525, it develops a distinctly sharper discontinuity at J 2 /J 1 = 0.51."
  ]
}